Paper: hep-th/9610010

Date: 1996-10-02

Title: Self-consistent determination of hard modes in hot QCD

Authors: A. Ni\'{e}gawa

Comments: 32pages, Figures are not included

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D55 (1997) 4997-5014; Erratum-ibid. D56 (1997) 2475

We determine self-consistently the hard-quark and hard-gluon modes in hotQCD. The damping-rate part in resummed hard-quark or hard-gluon propagators,rather than the thermal-mass part, plays the dominant role.